.Dd February 3, 2025
.Dt MKCONF 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mkconf
.Nd build system configuration script generator
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm mkconf
.Op Fl c Ar bconf
.Op Fl o Ar output
.Op Fl t Ar template-set
.Op Fl O Ar output-template
.Op Fl M Ar makefile-template
.Op Ar name Op Ar version
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Create a
.Ic configure
.Xr sh 1
script from a
.Xr bconf 5
build system description.
.Bl -tag
.It Fl c Ar bconf
Path of the
.Xr bconf 5
build options file, by default,
.Ar bconf .
.It Fl o Ar output
Path of the created configure script, by default,
.Ar configure .
.It Fl t Ar template-set
Name of the template set to use. If
.Ar template-set
contains a '/', it is considered a relative path where both
.Ar output-template
and
.Ar makefile-template
are looked respectively as
.Pa configure.in
and
.Pa GNUmakefile.in .
.Pp
Else it is considered relative to
.Nm
data installation directory. Its default
value depends on configuration, contact your
system administrator for the list of available
template sets.
.It Fl O Ar output-template
Path to a
.Pa configure
script template. If not specified, inferred from the provided
.Ar template-set .
.It Fl M Ar makefile-template
Path to a
.Pa GNUmakefile
template. If not specified, inferred from the provided
.Ar template-set .
.It Ar name
In the
.Pa GNUmakefile
generated by the
.Pa configure
script,
.Ic package-name
variable given to the package. Cannot be
empty, begin with a '.' or contain a '/' or a '-'.
.It Ar version
In the
.Pa GNUmakefile
generated by the
.Pa configure
script,
.Ic package-version
variable given to the package. If beginning with a 'v', the
letter is trimmed. If empty, replaced with "none". Cannot
contain a '/' or a '-'.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sh 1 , Xr gmake 1 , Xr bconf 5 .
